reviews.text: The museum has a good collection of medieval and Baroque art, though it is not presented in a way that makes it easy to follow or appreciate unless you're an expert. The fantastic Roman collection is still mostly in storage, though a small part has finally been returned to the Steinhalle (again the presentation is poor with little information and many objects hard to view).
Bit old fashion. English exist but not enough
Great Experience , nice pieces of art , lightening on paintings was perfect .

Magnificent collection organized by historical period and theme. I don't have a basis of comparison against other European galleries, but the baroque section was unlike anything I've seen at many major US city museums. Well worth the trip.
It was good for people who likes the history. Lots of paintings, statues. They offer route guide map and there are cloak rooms also.

Didn't visit the museum but the bar next to it. Can recommend: Very tasty spritzers and tasty beers. Atmosphere is great and staff was friendly. Only had to wait a bit long before they come take your order.
The Kunsthaus Graz, Grazer Kunsthaus is a museum of contemporary art built in 2003. I did not visit it, but the shape of this building immediately caught my eye because of its originality.
Architecturally, the Kunsthaus is a thing of beauty - a work of art. Inside is equally impressive. The exhibitions are nicely curated. 'Camera Austria' is currently displayed.
The breakfast was very good. The place deserves visiting.
good food , located near centre

No place around does the volume of meals as China Garden. It's a constant stop for Chinese tour buses on the weekend. Their dim sum is solid, but it's convenient if you're in DC or Arlington to get here compared to Falls Church or Silver Spring. The lady that runs the place can be a tad truculent, but she gives the place atmosphere.

Always feel free to reach out to me on Twitter @joerazz
Good Dim Sum food cart. It can get very busy during weekends due to tourist buses.  Excellent quality for Chinese party food. Unfortunately, they closed down in July 2017 and moved to Maryland.

Dim sum on a Saturday noon was surprisingly not busy.  The dumplings we're good, not great.  The roast duck was amazing, huge, fatty and full of flavor.  The ginger scallion lobster was also ok.  Service was very attentive.  Validated parking in the basement.

I used to be a motorcoach operator and brought many Asian Tour groups to this restaurant.
The food was always delicious. I was last at this restaurant in 2008.
If Asians eat at an Asian food establishment, the food has to be good. The food tastes just like quality restaurants in Chinatown, NYC

Pretty mediocre, but that might have been my bad for showing up right at the end of dim sum service. I got served cold squid, which luckily they replaced, and dumplings that had the stale texture of having been sitting out for hours. Would have been better if they had just told me no more dim sum.
I ordered a mild meal. Although I don’t like Spicy food, I do like my food flavorful. I felt that the mild dish I ordered was pretty bland, and could have had more flavor.

The food was pretty good, not the best indian I've had but good. Pretty good selection, not huge. Service was pretty good. The restaurant itself I found to be really cold and pretty small. Prices are very good, I think they are really fair. Overall good but I'm not dying to go back.
Absolutely wonderful place, fantastic options and delicious flavors. I wish I could go through the whole vegetarian menu - I haven't tried anything I haven't loved. Try the Masala tea!
The best Indian food in Iowa City, the Chicken Tikka Masala is the best. A great buffet selection with a lot of delicious Indian food.

This used to be our favorite place in IC. But it seems to have changed ownership or something over the course of the year. Each time we’ve gotten it the last few months, it has been disappointing in multiple ways. We kept trying it again because we’d loved it so much and were hoping it would get better again. But tonight was the last straw. Food was again very sub par and bad service. No more Masala for us and I don’t give it up lightly.
Nice Asian CH chain.  Good food, clean. Good service
Very good food and kind service

Simple, this place never fails to deliver and its great to be able to Swing backwards and forwards in your seat as you eat - Try it!! Its like being a child at a park! Beijing nights (Sweet and Sour Chicken) and rice is to die for and also their Pad Thai and fried rice. They also did like a Fried Chicken and fries which was like a KFC ,but obviously not KFC, but tasted better! :-D

I ordered online take away and when my husband got there they told us no order has been placed. Even though I received a confirmation. He was then quite left alone and had to ask a few times before they handled the matter.  Eventually, after 45min waiting, he finally got the food and still had to make his way home. I hoped at least the food was worth the waiting and the hastle, but the Vietnamese food was not authentic, you could smell that it was just beef-cube, and the noodles were still hard. I had to cook them again until they were edible... what if I were somewhere out?? what a pitty... would not order again.

This is our first visit since their upgrade. Great new menus, including the menu from their sister restaurant chain, Negishi and a drink menu with clever non-alcoholic options. We are certain to make this a regular haunt.

The staff are very nice, fast service, well curated menus: All would be perfect except for one thing. This may not bother some people, but it did concern me. If you need to use silverware, you have to take it out of a utensil bucket on the table. The spoons and forks are facing business end up. This means that when somebody pulls one out, the utensils next to them are being touched as well. Unless you just use chopsticks or order a large soup that comes with a spoon, you may be putting your mouth where a stranger put their hand :-(

Only some people would be bothered by this, but I really think they need to change how silverware is provisioned.

Other than that, the reinvented Nooch @ Barfi is a hard place to beat for Asian food in Basel.

Not as good as it used to be 4 years ago. I was looking forward to coming back and trying it again. I thought maybe it was just me but after reading other comments I know its not just me. Flavor is gone, mediocre food. Very little meat in my regular burrito which for me is just fine but there was also even less green chili. Great friendly service though.

My fiance and Father in law have been going here for years. Today was my first time and I loved it.
I ordered Huevos Rancheros with red Chile. Yummy yummy.
It was a trip for us but well worth it. I recommend adding this location to your "must stop" places.

These are the best new Mexican burritos around. You can't go wrong here. Try one of the meat or bean before going for the giant burrito thing. The giant one is good but you need to try the regular burritos to really know how good they are.
I think Albuquerque was built around this place. It has been here as long as I can remember. It serves a local version of Mexican fast food, which has always tasted great.
The food is good and the price is also good the service is quick  the location is not the best. It is if you work or live on military base. Even if you live in the hood.
